review:
One of the greatest disappointments I recently had. The game has nice graphics and visual style, some cool mood and music, but combat, physics, interactions are totally broken and even don't look like a beta, maybe a pre-alpha... namely:
- interactions often fail to execute;
- you can easily get stuck into any dynamic objects on the map;
- you can easily get stuck by an enemy near door (goblin in plate armor);
- combat is boring, dull and not engaging - very slow pacing;
- enemy attack animations are horrible and even my pixel art Unity demos look better;
- game has no dynamic action what-so-ever ;)
- the beginning of the game is very strange, tutorial seems a bit not inline with the surrounding and those keys you can see through the hole in the wall are luring, but you even can't interact with them;
- 'spell / magic system' is strange to use imho,
- the game's difficulty should increase over time imho,
- steep learning curve. 

In other words - I don't recommend it now. It has potential, but maybe you can check it out later, after some updates.
